The paper introduces a new dataset designed for training machine learning models of symbolic music data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper describes the preprocessing and cleaning pipeline, which includes the exclusion of a number of files based on scores from a previously developed probabilistic machine learning model. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper defines training, testing, and validation splits for the new dataset, based on a clustering scheme, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
